title: Traces
description: While attending an online forensic course, a young lab assistant discovers that the fictitious case study has a link to her past. With the help of two female professors she works on bringing a killer to justice.
description2: ["While Kathy oversees the excavation of Marie's grave, Daniel gives McKinven the lead he needs to make an arrest, but it's the exacting forensic science that finally brings peace for Emma. (Final)", "Daniel faces a culpable homicide charge for the fire and wants to protect Phil's reputation, but when Emma meets Phil for the first time, her instinct tells her to be wary of him.", "Emma's return to Dundee to start a new job brings her mother's unsolved murder into sharp focus as she fights to bring the killer to justice. However, before she makes the journey back to Dundee, a fatal fire in a nightclub proves an sinister omen.", "Emma's accusation against Phil drives a wedge between her and Daniel. McKinven urges Emma to stop sleuthing, as he's certain that the person who killed her mother is known to her.", "McKinven's enquiries ruffle feathers and a furious Julie chides Emma for dragging up the past. When Emma is threatened with a knife, it's clear that someone's hiding something.", "Kathy and Sarah work through the Secrets nightclub fire. Sarah's report has some damning things to say about the safety of the building, but after feeling overwhelmed by the police interest, she wonders what she's started."]
features: attending online forensic course young lab assistant discovers fictitious case study link past help two female professor work bringing killer justice
